cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Facadia, please cite it and the AnySplat paper it builds on."
title: "Facadia — the AI building surveyor"
abstract: >-
  Facadia reads a building façade from ordinary drone footage, measures each defect
  in millimetres with classical computer vision, has a vision-language model
  (Claude) grade and explain it against code-grounded severity standards, and drafts
  the legally required façade-inspection report — with a human Registered Inspector
  signing off. A 3D-reconstruction module turns the same footage into a navigable
  model (point cloud / Gaussian splat).
type: software
authors:
